verses.text_plain: And Moses spake unto the heads of the tribes concerning the children of Israel, saying, This is the thing which the Lord hath commanded.
verses.verse_html: 1And Moses spake unto the heads of the tribes concerning the children of Israel, saying, This is the thing which the Lord hath commanded.

verses.text_plain: If a man vow a vow unto the Lord, or swear an oath to bind his soul with a bond; he shall not break his word, he shall do according to all that proceedeth out of his mouth.
verses.verse_html:
2If a man vow a vow unto the Lord, or swear an oath to bind his soul with a bond; he shall not break his word, he shall do according to all that proceedeth out of his mouth. ▼
▼ break: Heb. profane

verses.text_plain: If a woman also vow a vow unto the Lord, and bind herself by a bond, being in her father’s house in her youth;
verses.verse_html: 3If a woman also vow a vow unto the Lord, and bind herself by a bond, being in her father’s house in her youth;

verses.text_plain: And her father hear her vow, and her bond wherewith she hath bound her soul, and her father shall hold his peace at her: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond wherewith she hath bound her soul shall stand.
verses.verse_html: 4And her father hear her vow, and her bond wherewith she hath bound her soul, and her father shall hold his peace at her: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond wherewith she hath bound her soul shall stand.

tokens.text: at her: then all her vows

verses.text_plain: But if her father disallow her in the day that he heareth; not any of her vows, or of her bonds wherewith she hath bound her soul, shall stand: and the Lord shall forgive her, because her father disallowed her.
verses.verse_html: 5But if her father disallow her in the day that he heareth; not any of her vows, or of her bonds wherewith she hath bound her soul, shall stand: and the Lord shall forgive her, because her father disallowed her.

verses.text_plain: And if she had at all an husband, when she vowed, or uttered ought out of her lips, wherewith she bound her soul;
verses.verse_html:
6And if she had at all an husband, when she vowed, or uttered ought out of her lips, wherewith she bound her soul; ▼
▼ she vowed: Heb. her vows were upon her

tokens.text: And if she had at all an husband

footnotes.body_text: ▼ she vowed: Heb. her vows were upon her
footnotes.body_html: ▼ she vowed: Heb. her vows were upon her

verses.text_plain: And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her in the day that he heard it: then her vows shall stand, and her bonds wherewith she bound her soul shall stand.
verses.verse_html: 7And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her in the day that he heard it: then her vows shall stand, and her bonds wherewith she bound her soul shall stand.

verses.text_plain: But if her husband disallowed her on the day that he heard it; then he shall make her vow which she vowed, and that which she uttered with her lips, wherewith she bound her soul, of none effect: and the Lord shall forgive her.
verses.verse_html: 8But if her husband disallowed her on the day that he heard it; then he shall make her vow which she vowed, and that which she uttered with her lips, wherewith she bound her soul, of none effect: and the Lord shall forgive her.

tokens.text: then he shall make her vow which she vowed

verses.text_plain: But every vow of a widow, and of her that is divorced, wherewith they have bound their souls, shall stand against her.
verses.verse_html: 9But every vow of a widow, and of her that is divorced, wherewith they have bound their souls, shall stand against her.

tokens.text: and of her that is divorced

verses.text_plain: And if she vowed in her husband’s house, or bound her soul by a bond with an oath;
verses.verse_html: 10And if she vowed in her husband’s house, or bound her soul by a bond with an oath;

verses.text_plain: And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her, and disallowed her not: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond wherewith she bound her soul shall stand.
verses.verse_html: 11And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her, and disallowed her not: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond wherewith she bound her soul shall stand.

tokens.text: her not: then all her vows

verses.text_plain: But if her husband hath utterly made them void on the day he heard them; then whatsoever proceeded out of her lips concerning her vows, or concerning the bond of her soul, shall not stand: her husband hath made them void; and the Lord shall forgive her.
verses.verse_html: 12But if her husband hath utterly made them void on the day he heard them; then whatsoever proceeded out of her lips concerning her vows, or concerning the bond of her soul, shall not stand: her husband hath made them void; and the Lord shall forgive her.

verses.text_plain: Every vow, and every binding oath to afflict the soul, her husband may establish it, or her husband may make it void.
verses.verse_html: 13Every vow, and every binding oath to afflict the soul, her husband may establish it, or her husband may make it void.

verses.text_plain: But if her husband altogether hold his peace at her from day to day; then he establisheth all her vows, or all her bonds, which are upon her: he confirmeth them, because he held his peace at her in the day that he heard them.
verses.verse_html: 14But if her husband altogether hold his peace at her from day to day; then he establisheth all her vows, or all her bonds, which are upon her: he confirmeth them, because he held his peace at her in the day that he heard them.

tokens.text: them, because he held his peace

verses.text_plain: But if he shall any ways make them void after that he hath heard them; then he shall bear her iniquity.
verses.verse_html: 15But if he shall any ways make them void after that he hath heard them; then he shall bear her iniquity.

tokens.text: But if he shall any ways

verses.text_plain: These are the statutes, which the Lord commanded Moses, between a man and his wife, between the father and his daughter, being yet in her youth in her father’s house.
verses.verse_html: 16These are the statutes, which the Lord commanded Moses, between a man and his wife, between the father and his daughter, being yet in her youth in her father’s house.
